**Phase 2 ✅ — Audit bestanden.** Weiter mit Phase 3.

---

## PHASE 3 — Nginx + PHP-FPM

### Step 3.1 — Default-Site deaktivieren

```bash
rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
```

### Step 3.2 — PHP-FPM Pool schreiben

```bash
cat > /etc/php/8.2/fpm/pool.d/velocms.conf <<'POOL'
[velocms]
user = velocms
group = www-data

listen = /run/php/php8.2-velocms.sock
listen.owner = www-data
listen.group = www-data
listen.mode = 0660

pm = dynamic
pm.max_children = 20
pm.start_servers = 4
pm.min_spare_servers = 2
pm.max_spare_servers = 8
pm.max_requests = 500

php_admin_value[error_log] = /var/log/velocms/php-fpm.error.log
php_admin_flag[log_errors] = on
php_admin_value[expose_php] = Off
php_admin_value[display_errors] = Off
php_admin_value[memory_limit] = 256M
php_admin_value[upload_max_filesize] = 10M
php_admin_value[post_max_size] = 12M
php_admin_value[disable_functions] = exec,passthru,shell_exec,system,proc_open,popen
php_value[session.save_handler] = files
php_value[session.save_path] = /var/lib/php/sessions
POOL
```

### Step 3.3 — Nginx-Vhost schreiben

```bash
cat > /etc/nginx/sites-available/velocms <<'NGINX'
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name webzite-newmedia.com www.webzite-newmedia.com;

    root /var/www/velocms/public;
    index index.php;
    charset utf-8;

    access_log /var/log/velocms/access.log;
    error_log  /var/log/velocms/error.log;

    # Security headers (HTTPS-only headers added by Certbot in Phase 4)
    add_header X-Frame-Options "SAMEORIGIN";
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff";
    add_header Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin";

    # Front controller
    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
    }

    # Tenant uploads (outside webroot, served via Nginx alias)
    location /storage/ {
        alias /storage/;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, max-age=2592000";
    }

    # PHP-FPM
    location ~ \.php$ {
        fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php/php8.2-velocms.sock;
        fastcgi_index index.php;
        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $realpath_root$fastcgi_script_name;
        include fastcgi_params;
        fastcgi_hide_header X-Powered-By;
        fastcgi_read_timeout 60;
    }

    # Static assets — long cache, DSGVO: only self-hosted assets here
    location ~* \.(css|js|jpg|jpeg|png|gif|ico|svg|webp|woff|woff2|ttf|eot)$ {
        expires 30d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }

    # Block dotfiles, env files, sensitive extensions
    location ~ /\. { deny all; }
    location ~ \.(env|md|lock|xml|yml|sh|sql)$ { deny all; }
}
NGINX
```

### Step 3.4 — Site aktivieren + beides neu starten

```bash
ln -sf /etc/nginx/sites-available/velocms /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/velocms && nginx -t && systemctl restart php8.2-fpm && systemctl reload nginx
```

### Double-Audit Gate — Phase 3 Verification

```bash
systemctl is-active nginx && systemctl is-active php8.2-fpm && ls -la /run/php/php8.2-velocms.sock
```

```bash
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "HTTP %{http_code} — %{time_total}s\n" http://95.217.185.113/admin/login
```

Erwartetes Ergebnis: `active` für beide Services, Socket-Datei vorhanden, HTTP-Status `200`.

---

Sobald du die Ausgabe einfügst, folgt Phase 4 (SSL + Security Hardening mit Certbot).
